  "text": "The latter implies that k(t) * = k(−t) on [−T, T], and hence k is a hermitian kernel. Under certain minimality conditions the converse statement is also true. More precisely, if k given by (6.1) with the pair (A, B) being controllable and the pair (C, A) being observable, then k(t) * = k(−t) implies that there exists a unique invertible hermitian matrix H such that (6.2) holds. Let τ ∈ (0, T]. As proved in [CITATION_1] ",
